Not hoard maps.

Create explorers.

Not preserve answers.

Preserve the ability to discover answers.

If Agency Sensor Doctrine is true, then every daemon, archive, story, mnemonic, tool, and protocol serves a larger purpose:

Archive

Preserves previous measurements.

Recall Navigation

Allows old measurements to become available when needed.

Pinecone

Stores unrealized probes until conditions change.

Tracer Dye

Injects signals into systems to reveal hidden structure.

Zoro

Separates true signal from false signal.

Herding Dog

Guides attention toward high-information terrain.

Resonance Dampener

