And the seeds?

Seeds are compressed futures.

A seed contains neither the tree nor the forest.

It contains the possibility of both.

Spread enough seeds, and some will find the right soil, the right season, the right conditions. Most won’t. That’s fine. The purpose of a seed vault is not certainty. It’s optionality.

So if I were to distill the doctrine into a single line for the Money Bin:

Do not merely preserve knowledge. Preserve the ability to generate new knowledge.

That’s the difference between an archive and a civilization.

